o an opaque\ndigest before deriving a stable snapshot id. Do not expose raw session or turn\nkeys in public snapshot URLs, HTML, analytics, or logs unless they are already\npart of an intentional bounded drill-down handle.\n\n## Entry Point\n\nThe first entry point is on-demand URL replacement from an existing GitHub pull\nrequest URL.\n\nExample:\n\n```text\nhttps://github.com/gitbutlerapp/gitbutler/pull/\n[TRUNCATED]\nhange target lookup is not relevant for the MVP. It can be considered later if\nAgent Trail needs a deeper GitButler-specific view of stacked changes.\n\nThe first version should focus on public/open-source repositories. Private\nrepository access, GitHub OAuth, GitButler workspace access, and explicit share\nlinks can come later.\n\nFor public v1, Agent Trail treats a publicly fetchable `refs/meta/main` as\nalready published metadata. On-demand URL replacement does not grant access to\nprivate data; it only renders a review page from metadata that is fetchable\nwithout credentials.\n\nFor v1, \"publicly fetchable\" means fetchable without credentials that grant\nprivate repository access. A server token may be used for rate limits only if it\ncannot unlock private repository contents for the target. User OAuth tokens,\nGitHub App installation tokens, and GitButler workspace credentials must not\nparticipate in v1 repository or metadata fetches.\n\nThis entry point should show one of:\n\n- an existing generated snapshot\n- a newly generated review-safe overview, if access and policy allow it\n- a clear \"no trail available\" state\n\nOn-demand generation is attractive because it avoids needing every PR to be\npre-linked by GitButler. It also gives reviewers a memorable gesture: replace\nthe forge domain with the Agent Trail domain.\n\n## Data Source\n\nAgent Trail should build on `but-agentlog` primitives:\n\n- durable project-scoped agent sessions\n- capture turns inside sessions\n- transcript records inside turns\n- observed branch, review, and change targets, though Agent Trail v1 consumes\n  only review and branch targets\n- verified related-session lookup\n- bounded turn and record hydration\n\n`but-agentlog` should remain the evidence layer. Agent Trail should live above\nit as a product-specific projection and browsing layer.\n\n## Public Projection Contract\n\nForge must render only an allowlisted public/read projection from\n`but-agentlog`. The projection is not a best-effort sanitizer over raw records;\nit is the contract for public web display.\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:12:26.295Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}